Patch Set 13:

Now that these are green, do we want to keep a variant that ensures we test this in some integrated fashion?

OTOH, I want to remain mindful of gate resources.

Thoughts?

Patch Set 13:

> Patch Set 13:
> 
> Now that these are green, do we want to keep a variant that ensures we test this in some integrated fashion?
> 
> OTOH, I want to remain mindful of gate resources.
> 
> Thoughts?

Yes, I was thinking about this last night. We could maybe we use the nova-ceph-multistore job for that, since it will get a *lot* of the surface area in one go. The only problem with that is that we might not notice if we break something with the default config, which will will break nova and not us. Not sure how much of a concern that is once this gets settled though.

Otherwise we could just pick one our -import jobs, which have a lot of import plugins configured. The -import-standalone maybe, since that is a leaf of the -import job and we can tweak its config without affecting anything else.
